9 Section 25. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
10 There is created the school building construction fund, to be administered by the
11 Department of School and Public Lands commissioner of school and public lands, for the
12 purpose of making loans to school districts to construct or expand a school building, as
13 provided in section 26 of this Act. The Subject to the provisions of this section, the
14 treasurer shall deposit in the fund two percent the first sixty million dollars of the taxes
15 collected pursuant to:
16 (1) Chapter 10-45;
17 (2) Chapter 10-46;
18 (3) Chapter 10-46E; and
19 (4) Chapter 10-58.
20 If two percent of the taxes collected pursuant to subdivisions (1) to (4), inclusive,
21 exceed sixty million dollars in a year, the treasurer shall deposit in the fund two percent
22 of the taxes collected pursuant to subdivisions (1) to (4), inclusive, in excess of sixty
23 million dollars, but not in excess of ninety million dollars.
24 Any interest earned on moneys in the fund must remain in the fund. Any repayment
25 of the principal amount of a loan must be deposited into the fund and used for making
26 new loans. Money in the fund designated for loans is appropriated through the general
27 appropriation bill for the purposes provided in section 26 of this Act.
28 The commissioner of the department shall approve vouchers, and the state auditor
29 shall draw warrants to pay expenditures authorized from this fund.
30 Section 26. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1281A 14 1281
1 The Department of School and Public Lands commissioner of school and public
2 lands may make loans from the school building construction fund, created in section 25 of
3 this Act, to a school district for the purpose of constructing or expanding a school building.
4 The amount of the loan may not exceed forty percent of the total cost of the construction
5 or expansion project. The department commissioner may use up to one percent of the
6 principal amount of a loan to offset the department's expenses in administering the loan.
7 Any loan made by the department commissioner must be provided to the district
8 at an interest rate of zero percent. The terms of the loan may not require collateral from
9 the district.
10 The terms of the loan must require that the payments be based on a straight and
11 level amortization of twenty years and be made annually over a term of twenty years,
12 with the first payment due one year from the date of the funding of the loan.
13 The department shall make available moneys from the school building construction
14 fund, created in section 25 of this Act, as follows:
15 (1) Thirty percent for the construction or expansion of a school building in a school
16 district that has four thousand or more students; and
17 (2) Seventy percent for the construction or expansion of a school building in all other
18 school districts.
19 The amount of loans made in a year under this section must exceed sixty-million
20 dollars and may not exceed ninety-million dollars.
21 For purposes of this section, a "school building" is a structure that houses the
22 academic instruction, extracurricular activities, and other functions of a kindergarten
23 through twelfth grade educational program.
24 Section 27. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
25 A school district is not eligible for a loan under section 26 of this Act if:
26 (1) The school district is eligible for a loan under § 11-15-8; or
27 (2) The municipality in which the district is headquartered is less than ten miles from
28 a municipality in which another school district is headquartered; or
29 (3) The school district has a fall enrollment of fewer than two hundred one hundred
30 fifty students and is not designated as a sparse school district, as defined in § 13-
31 13-78.
32 Section 28. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1281A 15 1281
1 The School Finance Accountability Board within the Department of Education shall
2 promulgate rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, specifying:
3 (1) The process by which:
4 (a) A school district applies for a loan;
5 (b) The Department of Education department reviews, assesses, and approves
6 a school district's application; and
7 (c) The Department of School and Public Lands commissioner of school and
8 public lands disburses a loan to a school district; and
9 (2) The information a school district must provide when applying for a loan pursuant
10 to section 26 of this Act, including:
11 (a) The amount of money currently in the district's capital outlay fund;
12 (b) The amount of money the district has transferred and the number of
13 transfers the district has made from the capital outlay fund, pursuant to
14 § 13-16-6 during the previous ten years;
15 (c) The district's current levy for the capital outlay fund;
16 (d) The district's fall enrollment for the current fiscal year; and
17 (e) The enrollment trends of the district during the previous ten years; and
18 (3) The criteria by which the Department of Education department assesses a school
19 district's application for a loan in accordance with section 26 of this Act, including:
20 (a) The minimum amount of money, in proportion to the district's fall
21 enrollment, that must currently be in a district's capital outlay fund;
22 (b) The maximum amount of money a district may have transferred from the
23 capital outlay fund, pursuant to § 13-16-6 during the previous ten years;
24 (c) The maximum levy a district may currently have set for the district's capital
25 outlay fund; and
26 (d) The minimum increase necessary in the district's capital outlay levy to be
27 sufficient for the district to repay the loan.
28 Section 29. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
29 On or before August first of each year, the Department of School and Public Lands
30 commissioner of school and public lands shall submit a report to the special committee,
31 created in § 4-8A-2, detailing the number, amounts, and recipients of loans provided by
32 the school building construction fund created in section 25 of this Act, and other relevant
33 information pertaining to the fund or program, as requested by the committee.
